        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-03-31 09:08:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > You don't have Honolulu branches created in https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ci-management/+/120040/, so why the cherry-pick?\n> \n> Okay. I was just modifying the existing csit files in the ci-management. I thought that we were running CSIT for both master and the current release. \n\nThis doesn't happen automatically, you need to explicitly define those in your template (see, for example, ccsdk-oran-csit definition in ci-management/jjb/ccsdk/ccsdk-csit.yaml)\n\n> Does this mean, previously CI didn't have a CSIT job for the branches\n\nYes",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
